## Audit Rules

- `present` means the resolved file or folder path currently contains at least one Firebase or Firestore text match.
- `not found` means the resolved file or folder path had no Firebase or Firestore text match at audit time.
- `unresolved` means the catalog label did not map cleanly to a live repo path and needs manual catalog cleanup or path clarification.
- Folder surfaces are checked recursively, so a parent surface can be marked `present` if any file under that surface still contains a Firebase or Firestore match.